import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Miles_per_Gallon'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Miles_per_Gallon'], errors='coerce')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['Miles_per_Gallon'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Miles_per_Gallon')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Miles_per_Gallon?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    plt.scatter(data['Displacement'], data['Weight_in_lbs'])
    plt.xlabel('Engine Displacement')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.ylabel('Weight in lbs')
    plt.title('How does the weight of the cars vary with their engine displacement?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['Cylinders'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the number of cylinders in the cars?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
